1
00:00:17,023 --> 00:00:19,123
Is that rumor true?

2
00:00:19,123 --> 00:00:20,335
What rumor?

3
00:00:20,335 --> 00:00:23,205
That Suho, Sieun, and you caught and turned in a gang member.

4
00:00:23,205 --> 00:00:25,230
That Free Money operator.

5
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:28,644
Oh, yes.

6
00:00:28,644 --> 00:00:30,412
Damn. That's dope.

7
00:00:30,412 --> 00:00:32,815
One of my friends lost several million won through that.

8
00:00:32,815 --> 00:00:35,050
So how did it happen? Come on. Spill it.

9
00:00:35,050 --> 00:00:38,577
- Please? I'm dying to know.
- Beomseok, what's your Instagram?

10
00:00:49,322 --> 00:00:51,323
Did you get home safely?

11
00:00:52,058 --> 00:00:54,726
Yes, I did.

12
00:00:54,726 --> 00:00:56,160
What about you?

13
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:58,363
I got home safely, too.

14
00:01:02,902 --> 00:01:04,670
They are freaking awesome.

15
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:35,544
Can you finish all that?

16
00:01:35,544 --> 00:01:38,213
Yes, and I'm going to get a snack too. Right, Beomseok?

17
00:01:38,213 --> 00:01:40,082
Sure, it's on me. You should join.

18
00:01:40,082 --> 00:01:43,218
You can't pay for us every day. I'll pay in full today.

19
00:01:43,218 --> 00:01:45,777
You're all dead. Brace yourselves.

20
00:01:46,679 --> 00:01:48,590
Do you guys have time this weekend?

21
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:50,859
I found a must-eat place. We should go.

22
00:01:50,859 --> 00:01:54,995
I can't resist delicious food. Let's go. Let's go.

23
00:01:56,789 --> 00:01:59,725
You're talking about food while eating food?

24
00:02:02,295 --> 00:02:06,565
Don't you ever talk about life while you're still living it?

25
00:02:11,671 --> 00:02:14,039
What about Yeongi's part-time job?

26
00:02:14,039 --> 00:02:16,408
She has an interview this weekend.

27
00:02:16,408 --> 00:02:19,011
It's good. They needed help anyway.

28
00:02:19,845 --> 00:02:22,948
- Who's Yeongi?
- You know that girl.

29
00:02:22,948 --> 00:02:25,450
The girl who hit the guy's head.

30
00:02:26,586 --> 00:02:29,698
Oh, right. Did you know her from before?

31
00:02:29,698 --> 00:02:31,322
No.

32
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:36,371
She's staying with him for a bit.

33
00:02:36,371 --> 00:02:38,555
Should we let her join us this weekend?

34
00:02:41,601 --> 00:02:44,436
Sure. I'm okay with it. I don't mind.

35
00:04:29,375 --> 00:04:31,075
How's your father?

36
00:04:32,945 --> 00:04:35,013
He's been busy lately.

37
00:04:35,013 --> 00:04:36,781
It's training season.

38
00:04:39,819 --> 00:04:41,953
Have you decided on a major?

39
00:04:45,057 --> 00:04:46,457
Not yet.

40
00:04:46,459 --> 00:04:49,461
That's okay. Take your time with it.

41
00:04:49,461 --> 00:04:51,897
I have no worries about you.

42
00:04:51,897 --> 00:04:54,166
You take care of things so well.

43
00:04:57,136 --> 00:04:59,371
There are lots I can't do.

44
00:05:00,573 --> 00:05:02,073
What was that?

45
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,280
Nothing.

46
00:05:15,655 --> 00:05:18,333
Are you done eating? Let's get coffee on our way out.

47
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:20,257
I have a meeting.

48
00:05:24,130 --> 00:05:25,730
Hello?

49
00:05:25,730 --> 00:05:27,665
I'm on my way.

50
00:05:27,665 --> 00:05:30,235
What should we do for your birthday?

51
00:05:30,235 --> 00:05:31,569
What should we do?

52
00:05:31,569 --> 00:05:35,474
You don't need to do anything. Let's just eat something together.

53
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:40,188
No, it's your birthday. We need to have freaking fun.

54
00:05:40,188 --> 00:05:42,581
I said I don't need anything, loser.

55
00:05:42,581 --> 00:05:44,583
Is it your birthday?

56
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:46,704
Yes, it's two Saturdays from now.

57
00:05:46,704 --> 00:05:49,988
- Should we rent a place for a party?
- Auntie,

58
00:05:49,988 --> 00:05:51,700
don't you need to be saving?

59
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:54,504
You said you were going to look for a room.

60
00:05:59,599 --> 00:06:02,501
They have so many drinks. What should I get?

61
00:06:03,636 --> 00:06:05,636
What do you want?

62
00:06:05,636 --> 00:06:07,382
I'll have an Iced Americano.

63
00:06:07,382 --> 00:06:10,709
I'll have an Iced Vienna coffee.

64
00:06:12,678 --> 00:06:14,379
Let's get a table.

65
00:06:15,348 --> 00:06:17,082
This looks good, right?

66
00:06:19,518 --> 00:06:21,219
Hey, sit here.

67
00:06:22,388 --> 00:06:24,356
Are you ready to order?

68
00:06:43,376 --> 00:06:44,976
Hey, Sieun.

69
00:06:47,213 --> 00:06:49,448
Hey, hurry up. Come sit over here.

70
00:06:49,448 --> 00:06:52,250
Why do you look so stylish today?

71
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,962
You trying to get me to like you?

72
00:06:53,962 --> 00:06:57,288
- It's working.
- Where have you been?

73
00:06:57,288 --> 00:06:58,755
Where were you?

74
00:06:58,755 --> 00:07:02,761
- I just had an appointment.
- What appointment?

75
00:07:02,761 --> 00:07:07,966
- Sieun is so freaking secretive.
- I know all the whereabouts of him.

76
00:07:09,302 --> 00:07:13,048
- Do not track my location.
- No. I'm going to see when you get home.

77
00:07:13,048 --> 00:07:14,783
Yes, check on Sieun.

78
00:07:14,807 --> 00:07:17,209
- Do you know WithMap?
- No.

79
00:07:18,244 --> 00:07:20,279
Beomseok, what are you doing?

80
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:33,800
[Park Ji Hoon]

81
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:36,490
[Choi Hyeon Wook]

82
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:39,200
[Hong Kyeong]

83
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,080
[Lee Yeon]

84
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:43,200
[Shin Seung Ho]

85
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,880
[WEAK HERO CLASS 1]
♫ The heart that you take out after passing ♫

86
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:49,570
♫ It's an old regret ♫

87
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:53,750
♫ It's already too late ♫

88
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:58,720
♫ Words I didn't want to hear ♫

89
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,800
♫ A face covered with a hand ♫

90
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:06,340
♫ I didn't know I'd miss you ♫

91
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:18,460
♫ I regret it, let's not cry anymore ♫

92
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:30,770
♫ Sigh. Please don't hide ♫

93
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:38,430
[Original: SeoPass - Kim Jin Seok "Weak Hero"]

94
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:46,108
♪ You're late. Why didn't you call sooner?

95
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:50,812
- ♪ Let's just meet during the day
- ♪ Let's just meet during the day

96
00:08:50,812 --> 00:08:55,283
♪ I know I'm going to regret it, but…

97
00:08:55,283 --> 00:08:57,553
♪ What are you up to?

98
00:08:57,553 --> 00:09:00,689
- ♪ Are you sleeping? Are you out?
- ♪ Are you sleeping? Are you out?

99
00:09:00,689 --> 00:09:05,427
- ♪ I'm sending these stupid texts to my ex
- ♪ I'm sending these stupid texts to my ex

100
00:09:05,427 --> 00:09:08,430
- ♪ I'm not suggesting anything
- ♪ I'm not suggesting anything

101
00:09:08,430 --> 00:09:12,935
♪ I'm just bored

102
00:09:12,935 --> 00:09:14,703
- Do you want a drink?
- What?

103
00:09:14,703 --> 00:09:17,439
- What do you want?
- I'll go with you.

104
00:09:17,439 --> 00:09:19,164
No, I'll just go.

105
00:09:50,229 --> 00:09:52,297
What? That's Oh Beomseok.

106
00:09:52,297 --> 00:09:54,066
- Oh Beomseok?
- Hey!

107
00:09:54,066 --> 00:09:55,544
Why would he be here?

108
00:09:55,544 --> 00:09:57,946
- It's true.
- Don't make things up.

109
00:09:57,946 --> 00:09:59,681
- I really saw him.
- Beomseok.

110
00:09:59,705 --> 00:10:01,116
Did he run away?

111
00:10:01,140 --> 00:10:04,176
- Beomseok? Where's my dear Beomseok?
- Beomseok can sing?

112
00:10:04,176 --> 00:10:07,012
- Oh Beomseok!
- Hey, try calling him.

113
00:10:30,269 --> 00:10:32,937
Yes. We're at a karaoke.

114
00:10:32,937 --> 00:10:36,541
- What room number are we in?
- I don't know.

115
00:10:37,543 --> 00:10:40,378
It's your friend. He's been calling non-stop.

116
00:10:42,848 --> 00:10:47,953
What the hell are you doing, you bitch? Why answer my phone without my permission?

117
00:10:48,921 --> 00:10:51,341
Hey, what's wrong? Why are you so mad?

118
00:10:51,341 --> 00:10:53,492
What? You want to hit me?

119
00:10:54,126 --> 00:10:55,661
Fuck you.

120
00:10:55,661 --> 00:10:59,597
Hey, stop it. Why so angry all of a sudden?

121
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:03,167
Hey, Beomseok.

122
00:11:05,104 --> 00:11:07,005
I said stop it.

123
00:11:12,878 --> 00:11:15,947
What's with this fucking bastard?

124
00:11:15,947 --> 00:11:17,648
Piss off.

125
00:11:17,648 --> 00:11:19,885
Hey. Wait!

126
00:11:21,287 --> 00:11:23,087
I'll go get her.

127
00:11:25,524 --> 00:11:27,392
Where are you going?

128
00:11:31,397 --> 00:11:33,297
Everything okay?

129
00:11:37,169 --> 00:11:40,272
Yes, I'm okay.

130
00:11:41,374 --> 00:11:44,019
- Hey, Beomseok.
- See? I told you I saw him.

131
00:11:44,019 --> 00:11:46,444
Here's my man. Beomseok, hey.

132
00:11:47,313 --> 00:11:49,247
How have you been?

133
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:52,251
Long time no see.

134
00:11:52,251 --> 00:11:54,186
We missed you.

135
00:11:57,089 --> 00:11:58,989
What is this?

136
00:11:58,989 --> 00:12:00,826
We're his friends.

137
00:12:03,663 --> 00:12:05,563
We were talking.

138
00:12:06,132 --> 00:12:09,201
We hadn't seen him in ages, so we wanted to talk as well.

139
00:12:10,603 --> 00:12:12,737
Then talk to him later.

140
00:12:18,210 --> 00:12:20,211
Okay. We're sorry.

141
00:12:20,211 --> 00:12:23,281
Let's catch up soon. I'll call you.

142
00:12:23,281 --> 00:12:25,884
Make sure you answer, okay?

143
00:12:26,953 --> 00:12:29,821
- Let's go.
- See you again.

144
00:12:29,821 --> 00:12:31,923
He still looks like a dork.

145
00:12:35,328 --> 00:12:36,928
Who are they?

146
00:12:38,164 --> 00:12:40,765
- What?
- Those guys.

147
00:12:42,468 --> 00:12:44,068
Right.

148
00:12:45,204 --> 00:12:47,239
They're just no one.

149
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:51,050
[Classroom 1-6]

150
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:07,525
Hey.

151
00:13:11,831 --> 00:13:13,231
Hey!

152
00:13:18,070 --> 00:13:19,670
Be quiet.

153
00:13:23,843 --> 00:13:26,111
I mean, shut your mouths.

154
00:13:33,586 --> 00:13:35,186
You're laughing?

155
00:13:35,755 --> 00:13:37,355
I wasn't laughing.

156
00:13:38,024 --> 00:13:42,727
You did just laugh. You moron. Do you want to die?

157
00:13:43,396 --> 00:13:45,396
Beomseok,

158
00:13:45,396 --> 00:13:47,264
what's wrong?

159
00:13:49,268 --> 00:13:51,880
It's because he thinks Suho and Sieun have his back.

160
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,504
What?

161
00:13:54,407 --> 00:13:58,220
Hey, move it. What's going on here? What's wrong?

162
00:13:58,220 --> 00:14:00,856
- I don't know. He's just being crazy.
- You piece of crap.

163
00:14:00,856 --> 00:14:03,392
Hey, stop it, please.

164
00:14:03,392 --> 00:14:05,527
- What the hell are you looking at?
- Hey.

165
00:14:05,527 --> 00:14:07,462
You cutie, why are you being so scary?

166
00:14:07,462 --> 00:14:09,855
Let's go to the store, Sieun.

167
00:14:11,924 --> 00:14:14,493
Don't put your hands on my shoulders.

168
00:14:15,995 --> 00:14:17,495
What?

169
00:14:26,939 --> 00:14:28,840
What's wrong with him?

170
00:14:50,263 --> 00:14:54,901
[Bastard3]

171
00:14:57,503 --> 00:15:01,207
[Bastard4]

172
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:13,050
[Bastard4]

173
00:15:50,556 --> 00:15:54,526
So how do you feel? Morning workouts are the best, right?

174
00:15:57,463 --> 00:16:00,065
Were you able to reach Beomseok?

175
00:16:02,802 --> 00:16:03,945
No.

176
00:16:03,945 --> 00:16:06,381
I wonder if something's happened.

177
00:16:06,381 --> 00:16:08,205
He's not answering my calls either.

178
00:16:08,205 --> 00:16:12,077
Do you want to drop by his place later today?

179
00:16:12,077 --> 00:16:14,679
Yes, we can do that.

180
00:16:15,581 --> 00:16:18,483
Now, get up!

181
00:16:18,483 --> 00:16:21,163
I thought I was just running. I need to do more?

182
00:16:21,163 --> 00:16:23,522
I told you. It's a lesson today.

183
00:16:23,522 --> 00:16:25,189
Just the basics.

184
00:16:28,227 --> 00:16:30,862
Your feet should be shoulder-wide,

185
00:16:30,862 --> 00:16:33,498
and they should be at a 45-degree angle.

186
00:16:33,498 --> 00:16:37,102
I said I don't need it. Go take a nap. You must be tired.

187
00:16:37,102 --> 00:16:39,804
Don't worry, and just do it.

188
00:16:43,542 --> 00:16:46,378
Always keep your chin down.

189
00:16:46,979 --> 00:16:49,014
Put your fists like this.

190
00:16:49,014 --> 00:16:50,893
Always protect your chin with your arms.

191
00:16:50,893 --> 00:16:54,319
Okay? Remember. Protect your chin.

192
00:16:56,022 --> 00:16:58,400
Next, pretend there's someone in front of you.

193
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:01,627
He's threatening you and trying to beat you up.

194
00:17:01,627 --> 00:17:06,264
In that case, look at the opponent's shoulders, not his eyes.

195
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:09,368
Look at me like this.

196
00:17:11,337 --> 00:17:13,397
Just keep your eyes on their shoulders.

197
00:17:13,397 --> 00:17:15,884
When their shoulders seem to come toward you,

198
00:17:15,884 --> 00:17:18,577
just bend your body 90 degrees.

199
00:17:19,278 --> 00:17:21,657
Then hold their knees and knock them down.

200
00:17:21,657 --> 00:17:23,682
One, two, three.

201
00:17:25,518 --> 00:17:27,386
That was a takedown.

202
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:31,256
After you knock them down, you go like…

203
00:17:32,758 --> 00:17:35,460
Don't go right. Run away instead.

204
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:37,429
Don't even look back.

205
00:17:39,365 --> 00:17:42,634
Just run while the opponent is on the floor.

206
00:17:42,634 --> 00:17:44,903
Don't fight. You might get hurt.

207
00:17:48,074 --> 00:17:49,574
Got it?

208
00:17:58,417 --> 00:18:01,653
This is it, right? This is freaking awesome.

209
00:18:06,926 --> 00:18:09,127
What brings you guys here?

210
00:18:11,564 --> 00:18:13,932
Why is your phone off?

211
00:18:15,268 --> 00:18:18,770
I didn't know. Come in.

212
00:18:18,770 --> 00:18:22,275
Why didn't you come to school? What is it?

213
00:18:23,576 --> 00:18:25,577
Your house is freaking awesome.

214
00:18:25,577 --> 00:18:27,679
I just didn't feel well.

215
00:18:27,679 --> 00:18:29,590
You can wear those.

216
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:31,920
No wonder why you're so slim.

217
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:34,919
Just walking around the house is exercise.

218
00:18:34,919 --> 00:18:36,688
Why is your house so big?

219
00:18:37,456 --> 00:18:39,400
Is this an eternity plant or something?

220
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:43,800
You know, the ones that are supposed to bring you wealth.

221
00:18:43,804 --> 00:18:45,831
This is crazy.

222
00:18:45,831 --> 00:18:48,544
Isn't this too big? It's as big as my house.

223
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:50,569
Are you feeling sick?

224
00:18:51,604 --> 00:18:53,315
No, it's okay.

225
00:18:53,315 --> 00:18:54,616
I'm okay.

226
00:18:54,616 --> 00:18:57,319
Your mother is seriously beautiful.

227
00:18:57,319 --> 00:18:59,945
Your family looks so happy here.

228
00:18:59,945 --> 00:19:02,614
You all look like each other.

229
00:19:02,614 --> 00:19:04,382
They're not my family.

230
00:19:07,820 --> 00:19:11,099
My father adopted me publicly when he became a politician.

231
00:19:11,099 --> 00:19:13,458
It was strategic.

232
00:19:19,165 --> 00:19:21,099
Want something to drink?

233
00:19:29,842 --> 00:19:31,642
Is something wrong?

234
00:19:33,045 --> 00:19:35,123
- What? No, nothing's wrong.
- Hey.

235
00:19:35,123 --> 00:19:37,226
What is it?

236
00:19:37,226 --> 00:19:39,718
Come on. Tell me everything.

237
00:19:41,621 --> 00:19:43,121
Is it…

238
00:19:44,256 --> 00:19:47,326
about those guys we met at the karaoke the other day?

239
00:19:48,828 --> 00:19:51,296
- Is it about them?
- Karaoke?

240
00:19:51,296 --> 00:19:53,264
What karaoke?

241
00:20:07,246 --> 00:20:08,724
Hey, move over.

242
00:20:08,724 --> 00:20:10,448
Move.

243
00:20:10,448 --> 00:20:12,483
Stand at ease.

244
00:20:12,483 --> 00:20:16,788
- I said to stand at ease, you mongrel.
- Hurry up!

245
00:20:16,788 --> 00:20:19,134
- Do we need to beat you more?
- We went too easy.

246
00:20:19,134 --> 00:20:20,469
- Here I go.
- Go hard.

247
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:22,661
- Let's go, come on.
- Yes.

248
00:20:22,661 --> 00:20:24,195
Nice!

249
00:20:25,965 --> 00:20:27,233
- He's crying again?
- What a lowlife.

250
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:28,844
- Crying again?
- Stop pretending like it hurts.

251
00:20:28,844 --> 00:20:30,679
- Hey.
- Hey, Beomseok.

252
00:20:30,703 --> 00:20:32,948
Make sure you tell your father again, okay?

253
00:20:32,948 --> 00:20:36,118
Hey, let's get out of here. Beating him up is no fun.

254
00:20:36,118 --> 00:20:38,310
Let's go get some food.

255
00:20:42,982 --> 00:20:45,117
I was bullied…

256
00:20:46,352 --> 00:20:48,387
at my previous school.

257
00:20:49,088 --> 00:20:51,023
So because of them…

258
00:20:52,091 --> 00:20:54,426
I had to get therapy.

259
00:20:54,426 --> 00:20:57,213
And that's also why I transferred to this school.

260
00:20:58,297 --> 00:21:03,335
After I ran into them at the karaoke the other day, they keep calling me,

261
00:21:03,335 --> 00:21:04,870
asking me to come out.

262
00:21:06,939 --> 00:21:08,940
